# ORIG TITLE    US: nineteen injured in Mother’s Day parade shooting . 
# ORIG CONTENT  Nineteen people, including two children, have been shot in New Orleans. Gunfire erupted at a Mother’s Day parade on Sunday. Ten men, seven women and a girl and a boy – both aged 10 – were hit, according to police. The children were grazed and are said to be in good condition. Two other victims are undergoing surgery. It was unclear if those injured were marching or bystanders watching the parade. Police are searching for three suspects. 
